WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.262
There are distinct differences between Low-Context and High-Context cultures. In

00:00:05.262 --> 00:00:10.524
Low-Context cultures, such as Germany or the US, trust is

00:00:10.524 --> 00:00:15.786
built primarily through task completion. Communication is direct, explicit, and

00:00:15.786 --> 00:00:21.048
transparent. In High-Context cultures, such as Japan or Brazil, trust

00:00:21.048 --> 00:00:26.310
is built through relationship-oriented social connection. Communication is nuanced and

00:00:26.310 --> 00:00:31.572
layered to preserve social harmony. A tempting assumption is to

00:00:31.572 --> 00:00:36.834
treat all cultures the same, believing that direct honesty is

00:00:36.834 --> 00:00:42.096
universally appreciated. The better cue is to observe whether a

00:00:42.096 --> 00:00:47.358
culture prioritizes task completion or social connection. By showing these

00:00:47.358 --> 00:00:52.620
side-by-side, the correction is clear: adapting communication style to the

00:00:52.620 --> 00:00:57.882
specific cultural context prevents strategic failure. Recognizing this distinction is

00:00:57.882 --> 00:01:03.144
a strong strategy for global leadership.
